===Etymology===
Named after [[Austrian]] scientist Baron Sigmund Zois von Edelstein (1747-1819) in 1805.<ref>Richard V. Gaines, H. Catherine W. Skinner, Eugene E. Foord, Brian Mason, and Abraham Rosenzweig: ''Dana's new mineralogy'', John Wiley & Sons, 1997</ref>

===Noun===
'''zoisite'''

#{{mineralogy}} A [[mineral]] with [[orthorhombic]] crystals, [[calcium|Ca]]<sub>2</sub>[[aluminum|Al]]<sub>3</sub>([[silicon|Si]][[oxygen|O]]<sub>4</sub>)(Si<sub>2</sub>O<sub>7</sub>)O(O[[hydrogen|H]]).

